The paper deals with person re-identification using both vision and language information, which falls under computer vision (cs.CV) and natural language processing (cs.CL) sub-categories. The proposed approach involves a two stream deep convolutional neural network framework, which is a popular technique in machine learning (cs.LG) and multimedia (cs.MM) research. The paper also involves retrieval and correlation analysis, which are common techniques in information retrieval (cs.IR) research.
